    │   └── AdminHandler.java
    │
    └── util/
        ├── HttpUtil.java
        ├── JsonUtil.java
        └── Result.java                → generic Result<T> wrapper













        users                  → all persons (role determines type)
        doctors                → doctor-specific data (specialization, etc)
        patients               → patient-specific data (blood group, etc)
        nurses                 → nurse-specific data (ward, etc)
        verification_tokens    → email verification links
        refresh_tokens         → refresh token storage with rotation
        blacklisted_tokens     → invalidated JWT access tokens
        appointments           → bookings between doctor and patient
        bills                  → generated per appointment
        audit_logs             → every auth event logged
        rate_limit             → failed login attempts per email
        ```

        ---

        ## All API Endpoints
        ```
        Auth (public):
        POST   /auth/register          → register any role
        GET    /auth/verify?token=xxx  → verify email
        POST   /auth/login             → login → get JWT + refresh token
        POST   /auth/refresh           → rotate refresh token → new JWT
        POST   /auth/logout            → logout single device
        POST   /auth/logout/all        → logout all devices

        Doctors (DOCTOR + ADMIN):
        GET    /doctors                → list all doctors
        GET    /doctors/{id}           → get doctor profile
        PUT    /doctors/{id}           → update profile
        GET    /doctors/{id}/schedule  → view schedule
        GET    /doctors/{id}/appointments → view appointments

        Patients (PATIENT + DOCTOR + ADMIN):
        GET    /patients               → list (ADMIN only)
        GET    /patients/{id}          → get patient profile
        PUT    /patients/{id}          → update profile
        GET    /patients/{id}/bills    → view bills

        Nurses (NURSE + ADMIN):
        GET    /nurses                 → list nurses
        GET    /nurses/{id}            → get nurse profile
        PUT    /nurses/{id}            → update profile

        Appointments (all roles):
        POST   /appointments           → book appointment (PATIENT)
        GET    /appointments           → list (filtered by role)
        GET    /appointments/{id}      → get one
        PUT    /appointments/{id}      → update status (DOCTOR)
        DELETE /appointments/{id}      → cancel (PATIENT or ADMIN)

        Billing (ADMIN + DOCTOR):
        POST   /bills                  → generate bill
        GET    /bills/{id}             → get bill
        GET    /patients/{id}/bills    → all bills for patient

        Admin:
        GET    /admin/users            → all users
        GET    /admin/audit            → auth event log
        GET    /admin/stats            → system statistics
        ```

        ---

        ## The Build Order — Step by Step
        ```
        Phase 1 — Foundation
          Step 1  → pom.xml + database tables
          Step 2  → enums (UserRole, AppointmentStatus, BloodGroup, Specialization)
          Step 3  → custom exceptions
          Step 4  → interfaces (Schedulable, Billable, Auditable, Notifiable)
          Step 5  → Result<T> generic wrapper
          Step 6  → abstract Person + Doctor, Patient, Nurse models
          Step 7  → remaining models (Appointment, Bill, tokens)

        Phase 2 — Auth Infrastructure
          Step 8  → JwtUtil (RS256 key generation + sign + verify)
          Step 9  → PasswordUtil + RateLimiter
          Step 10 → EmailService (JavaMail SMTP)
          Step 11 → stores (UserStore, TokenStore, VerificationStore)

        Phase 3 — Auth Flows
          Step 12 → AuthService (register, verify, login, refresh, logout)
          Step 13 → AuthHandler + AuthMiddleware + RoleMiddleware

        Phase 4 — Hospital Features
          Step 14 → PersonFactory + remaining stores
          Step 15 → AppointmentService + BillingService
          Step 16 → all handlers (Doctor, Patient, Nurse, Appointment, Billing, Admin)

        Phase 5 — Wire Up
          Step 17 → Router + Main
          Step 18 → Full test flow
        ```

        ---

        ## New Things You Will Learn in This Project
        ```
        vs what you already know from Credit Risk + Inventory:

        Already know:
          ✅ HttpServer, routing, handlers
          ✅ PostgreSQL with JDBC
          ✅ BCrypt password hashing
          ✅ UUID tokens
          ✅ Jackson JSON

        New in this project:
          🆕 RSA key pairs — generate once, sign JWTs with private key
          🆕 JWT structure — header.payload.signature
          🆕 Abstract classes — Person cannot be instantiated directly
          🆕 Interfaces — contracts that classes must honour
          🆕 Enums — type-safe constants with behaviour
          🆕 Custom exceptions — meaningful errors with context
          🆕 Generics — Result<T> works for any type
          🆕 Design patterns — Factory, Strategy, Observer
          🆕 Services layer — business logic separated from handlers
          🆕 Role-based access — JWT claims carry user role
          🆕 Token rotation — refresh tokens replaced on every use
          🆕 Token blacklisting — invalidated JWTs tracked until expiry
          🆕 Email sending — JavaMail with SMTP
          🆕 Rate limiting — in-memory attempt tracking per email